FYI . Attached is a presentation on gas markets that I gave to an electricity group yesterday . The group was formed out of California's restructuring legislation ( AB 1980) . It's called the "AB 1980 Implementation Group" ( I heard that the group decided that its time to change its name.) . The group includes just about all of the interest groups in California . I focused on the fact that gas offers a model of a "real" market that California should look to in order to fix the "artificial" and failed electricity model created by AB 1980 . Best , Jeff
