Yes , the utilities can pass through the gas costs . They face an "incentive ratemaking mechanism" that includes a "market benchmarket" that they must meet or beat . The benchmark's a composite of spot indeces . So as long as they buy spot , they can meet the benchmark and pass everything through . ( Ill-conceived procurement incentive , particularly in these days when prices are going north , but at least there's no price cap creating gas undercollections like there is on the electric side. ) If you need anything else , just holler . Jeff
