The way we handled it last time was 1 ) have a quick chat about it , 2 ) split up the pieces , 3 ) once written , pass around the pieces to see if anyone has any strong feelings about what folks had pulled together , and then , for each case , 4 ) designate one person as the "assembler" of the pieces . ( We designated who would be responsible for which cases at the beginning of the semester. ) And yes , all by email ( save for , say , the preliminary chat) . It worked well . But I'm flexible , if folks want to try another angle . Best , Jeff
