I'm on vacation next week , but would be happy to get together first thing the following week to discuss . Also , in response to a voicemail that I received , wanted to let folks know that the CPUC did not hold gas hearings today . The legislature is , however , holding hearings , taking a "comprehensive view" of the industry ( i.e. , focusing on specific allegations of pipeline capacity "price gouging") . They held their first hearing today , but it got cut short due to activities underway in the Legislature . I believe that , prior to cutting the hearing short , the Legislature only made it through two panels of customers , who told stories of skyrocketing bills and associated hardship . One panel participant ( Anastacio Andrade of Sunrise Mushrooms , I believe ) waived an EES bill and described how it tripled between November and December . I have a feeling that the Legislature's actions may be prompting the PUC to appear that it's doing something . I'll report more on the Legislative hearings as they occur . Best , Jeff
