Here's how I think this thing has played ( is playing ) out: PG&E was very tactical . They knew that the Edison deal was imminent . They see the Edison deal as extremely adverse to their interests . They feared that the pressure on them to do the same deal would be enormous once the Governor announced the Edison deal . Thus , in an incredibly dramatic attempt to pre-empt the possibility that they'd have to accept the Edison deal , PG&E threw itself into bankruptcy . ( Preemption seems to have been very successful , at least at this point. ) So I think that they wanted everyone to know , including Wall Street and the Governor , that the decision's been made---they're going the way of Ch . 11 , not the way of J . Bryson and Edison . This make sense ? Best , Jeff
