Dudes: Here's my my comments to Mark's answers to the questions , and suggestions to Jimmie's model . I don't answer the bottom line question , since we have some talking to do on the model . Jimmie , your model is great except we have to value the company on cash flow ( as opposed to NI) . I've take a stab at setting up the discounted cash flow model . All my stuff is highlighted in yellow . It's the capex that's screwy ( see assumptions given in questions) . I get at 25% of 1995 revs , not 45.8% as indicated in the assumptions . I also assume that when it sez working capital is net zero , we don't factor those balance sheet line items into the DCF model . Others agree ? Anyway , it gives me a $3.32 share value , so I think the model's got some work . Take a look and let me know what you think . Best , Jeff
