Frank , By not being able to trade C$ denominated products we would not be able to trade most of the physical products including cash , one month , index gas , or be able facilitate long term structures . Having said that , if the time period for not trading these products was only 45 days , they could get past that without any major damage being done . It will take longer to get physical contracts in place in Canada than it will financial . The extra time the Canadian office would have before it traded physical C$ products would allow them to obtain a critical mass of trading counter parties . If it was going to be 120 or 180 days , then there would be problems . I hope this helps , let me know if you need any else . Regards , Jon
